      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IMA BOXA (10) is a lightly-raced but highly progressive pacer who made it six wins and a second from just seven starts when cruising home in his heat at this circuit and distance last week, drawing on this row but working to front and going on to score by 13m. That performance suggests he is a class above these. Looks the winner. IDEAL IN DREAMS (7) produced a series of solid efforts in higher-graded city races before winning her heat last week, taking her strike rate at this circuit and distance to 50 per cent. Draws on the back row but should enjoy a nice trail. Can be in the finish if she gets the gaps. WITHDISTINCTION (2) drew wider and had to work so was brave in winning his heat last week. A low draw should see him involved again. SIREN SEA (8) draws on the back row but is quite consistent so deserves a place in the first four.",
